texts.text: This is a list of Java Edition 1.7.4 development versions.
13w47a is the first snapshot released for Java Edition 1.7.4.

Microphone can be recorded too.
Chat integration in the game.[2]
Twitch related settings.[3]
Twitch Broadcast Settings:
Quality, Framerate, Bandwidth, Send Metadata, Mic Volume, System Volume, Compression, Enable Chat and User Filter (for the Twitch chat).

Super Secret Settings
New "Notch" shader added.
New Mojang Logo shows on game startup.

13 issues fixed
From released versions before Java Edition 1.7.4

MC-12413 – Furnace GUI - "full" arrow texture always drawn on leftmost column.
MC-14323 – Minimising other windows open resizes Minecraft window.
MC-23132 – Click or right-click stuck on OS X.
MC-26102 – OS X Fullscreen is not supported.
MC-30537 – Flower duplication glitch.
MC-31388 – Right clicking a flower pot that has certain plants in it while holding another plant replaces the one in the flower pot with the one the player is holding.
MC-35643 – Items with enchantment effect cause blocks and potion effects indicator to not render.
MC-35658 – Water is too transparent.
MC-35797 – Background rendering issues when picking up enchanted items/caption of containers white.
MC-36383 – Translucent parts of stained glass not visible in 3rd person mode.
MC-36395 – Weird rendering of transparent blocks on the 0-axis.
MC-36705 – Block held in 3rd person rendered incorrectly.
MC-37106 – All the textures are flipped/mirrored on north/east sides of blocks.
13w47b is the second snapshot for Java Edition 1.7.4, which was released to fix a crash in the 13w47a snapshot.

1 issue fixed
From the previous development version
13w47c is the third snapshot for Java Edition 1.7.4, which was released to fix some of the bugs and crashes in the 13w47a and 13w47b snapshots.

13w47c has no bug fixes.
13w47c was previously removed from the launcher for some time, but was added back in September 2018.
13w47d is the fourth snapshot for Java Edition 1.7.4, which was released to fix some of the bugs and crashes in the 13w47a, 13w47b and 13w47c snapshots.

4 issues fixed
From the Java Edition 1.7.4 development versions

MC-35296 – Draw order-related graphical errors involving stained glass.
MC-35561 – Players can see a stained glass pane clearer through stained glass.
MC-35694 – Stained glass texture different while in Creative-"Survival Inventory".
MC-40255 – Falling invisible slime causes "blue screen".
13w47e is the fifth snapshot for Java Edition 1.7.4, which was released to fix some of the bugs and crashes in the 13w47a, 13w47b, 13w47c and 13w47d snapshots.

5 issues fixed
From the Java Edition 1.7.4 development versions

MC-40512 – Stained glass panes are opaque in 3rd person mode.
MC-40527 – Twitch broadcast: Unknown error.
MC-40603 – 13w47c crashes at startup on Mac.
MC-40627 – Glass blocks in hotbar toggle backface culling on/off when selecting/deselecting a stained glass block.
13w48a is the sixth snapshot released for Java Edition 1.7.4.

13 issues fixed
From released versions before Java Edition 1.7.4

MC-190 – Misaligned textures on south and east faces for non-full blocks.
MC-16259 – Enchantments not showing stats in tooltip.
MC-29469 – Unable to take screenshot in GUI or active chat line.
MC-31006 – Adventuring Time — list of visited biomes resets on login.
MC-31651 – Block break animations no longer display.
MC-36159 – Graphical glitch on beacon effects in inventory screen.
MC-36772 – Enchanted items have big enchant around whole item.
From the Java Edition 1.7.4 development versions

MC-40580 – Changing a control to "Start Stream" key activates streaming.
MC-40621 – Flowing water surface not visible seen from inside flowing water blocks.
MC-40628 – There is no space between potion effect name & level.

MC-40647 – OpenGL greater than 1.5 but can't stream.
MC-40659 – Chest Texture flickers when looking at a dropped chest item.
MC-40718 – Shift + CapsLock / Volume buttons on Keyboard cause Twitch API to crash.
13w48b is the seventh snapshot for Java Edition 1.7.4, which was released to fix some of the bugs and crashes in the 13w48a snapshot.

Naming a sheep "jeb_" (with a name tag) will make the sheep wool fade between the different dye colors in order (like a rainbow effect).
Shearing produces the color wool the sheep had before it was named.

3 issues fixed
From released versions before Java Edition 1.7.4

MC-35897 – Damaged armor, tools & weapons placed in certain inventory slots cause other slots to go black.
MC-36482 – Upon exiting (shift-click) minecart, the range and criteria is drastically off, up to 8 blocks away.
13w49a is the eighth and final snapshot released for Java Edition 1.7.4, and the final snapshot of 2013.

Consist of a baby zombie riding a chicken.
The zombie controls the chicken instead of using the chicken AI.
Because the zombie is riding a chicken, it cannot take fall damage.
Extremely rare to find.

4 issues fixed
From released versions before Java Edition 1.7.4

MC-31622 – Wrong render distance on 9 and more chunks settings.
MC-41165 – SetSlot packet can no longer set item under cursor.
MC-41407 – Minor optimization to world generation.
MC-41508 – Hopper: java.lang.IllegalStateException: Not a JSON Object.
1.7.3 is the first and only pre-release for Java Edition 1.7.4,[4] released on December 6, 2013.[5]

11 issues fixed
From released versions before Java Edition 1.7.4

MC-5002 – Some texts cannot be translated in a language file.
MC-11129 – Unicode font text shadow in fullscreen mode.
MC-13046 – Certain supported characters glitch out, clearing out lines of text.
MC-32322 – World loading screen uses wrong font.
MC-33035 – Loading text in Polish (and other languages with Unicode font) isn't showing properly.
MC-34573 – Font file of Unicode page C2 (Korean) shows character '숼'(U+C23C) at the position of '쉴'(U+C274).
MC-41135 – Players become invisible and immune for PvP damage after being killed and relogging instead of respawning.
From the Java Edition 1.7.4 development versions
MC-40587 – Broadcast server list giving same values.

MC-41528 – No taskbar workbench icon in Windows.
MC-41537 – Hopper don't suck items from above if all the slots have an item.
MC-41566 – When the zombie chicken jockey is killed, chicken still attacks.
"It's here! Minecraft 1.7.3 pre-release is available for download, to be released early next week." – @Dinnerbone on Twitter, December 6, 2013
